 It is a standard way of getting into heavily-warded areas, though most people
 use magic items thrown into the area instead of creating a microscopic gate
 like I did."

\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
"I presume this is because they can't create a gate like that, even a tiny
 one," Zorian said.

\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
"Yes," Xvim confirmed.
 "But I'm hardly unique in this capacity, so it would be best to know how to
 deal with the tactic."

\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
"Fine," Zorian said wearily.
 "I admit defeat, master.
 I don't know how to ward against teleportation effectively, so please teach me
 how.
 And if possible, I'd also like to know how to make the micro-gate thing, too."

\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
"I suspect that level of skill is still beyond you, my student," Xvim told him
 with a small smile.
 "But we'll see.
 Now listen closely…"

\end_layout

